parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the anti-theft system can cause the vehicle to become stranded, leaving the driver stranded and potentially causing safety risks.
symptoms: The vehicle becomes immobilized
unable to start or move
due to issues with the anti-theft device.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the electrical system can cause a loss of critical vehicle functions, such as steering, braking, and lighting, which can lead to accidents or loss of control.
symptoms: The dashboard lights go out
the steering wheel locks up
the brakes fail
and the vehicle loses control; the key becomes stuck in the ignition.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The engine stalling and computer shutdown can cause the vehicle to lose power and stall, potentially leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The vehicle stalls while driving at high speeds
the computer shuts down
and the vehicle loses power.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the rear lighting system can cause reduced visibility, potentially leading to accidents or safety risks.
symptoms: The rear lights
dashboard lights
radio
and exterior lighting fail or malfunction
causing reduced visibility and safety risks.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake lines can cause a loss of brake fluid, leading to a loss of braking ability, which can increase the risk of accidents and injuries.
symptoms: The brake pedal travels to the floor
brake fluid leaks or ruptures excessively
the vehicle is unable to stop or slow down
the ABS system fails to activate
the vehicle pulls to one side while braking.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ABS system can cause the vehicle to lose traction, leading to accidents and injuries, especially on wet or slippery roads.
symptoms: The vehicle does not stop or slow down on wet pavement
the ABS system does not activate
the vehicle pulls to one side while braking.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the passenger side door hinge can cause the door to become detached from the vehicle, leading to a safety concern as the door may not close properly, and in extreme cases, may fall off while the vehicle is in motion.
symptoms: The door is almost completely detached from the vehicle
the door is inoperable
the door will not close completely
the hinges are badly cracked
the welds on the hinges are broken.
